<br>
I am a newly registered user of this board, but have been lurking for some time, and have found the information that I have gathered here to be invaluable to me.  Kudos to Graffe on an excellent site!  Anyway...  I will be clearing level 24 soon, and I am eager to start on some quests.  The only problem is that from the looks of things, most quests are geared toward  wizards above level 30.  I was curious if any of you had any suggestions on what sort of quests I could be looking at at level 24, and if so, what sort of tips you had to make these quests a bit smoother.  Also, any ideas on where I should be hunting at the moment?  SK is getting crowded and old....and because of the large number of people, spawns are frequently contested.<br>
<br>
Thank you for your help... <p><b>Arundel Pajo</b><br>
<i>Elven Dominion</i><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwalpus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>walpus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/26/00 8:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questing for lower mid levels...</span><hr size=1> I would like to know this too, quests and a place to hunt, I guess I'll be heading to SK in a while too, as I am lvl 19 right now, but have heard a lot of similar things aobut crowds.... oh yeah... people keep telling me places in kunark to fight but I dont' have it :v( <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uxaxia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xaxia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/27/00 3:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questing for lower mid levels...</span><hr size=1> If you're over 20, I'd highly recommend doing the Staff of the Wheel quest.  You DO NOT need to be 30+, and you DO NOT need the help of a guild or a group of 50+.  You definitely WILL need some help along the way, but the quest is really loads of fun.   You get an item that gives you +10 INT and +10 mana and a sense of accomplishment and self-worth as a wizard.<br>
<br>
I did this quest over 3 days with another wizard who is level 16.  You do need to ask magicians for waterstones along the way (every rod has something to do with water) and support from friends is helpful.  Stillnight, a lvl 51 wizardess helped me trememdously and gave me mucho support along the way.  Hiya, Stillnight!<br>
<br>
Besides the hand room rod, every one is obtainable solo.  I died twice going for the Lake Rathe one, once for the Oasis one, and once for the Everfrost one.  If I had wolf-form, I definitely could have survived Rathe and Oasis, not sure about EF.  But my point is that you don't need loads of help doing this quest.  Support is great though.<br>
<br>
I would recommend getting the easier rods first:  Qeynos aqueducts, Neriak, High Pass, etc.  Then go for the harder ones.  Be prepared to die at least a couple of times.  I know some of you out there didn't die once, but for us average folks, a couple of deaths is the norm.<br>
<br>
Follow Graffe's spoiler and do this quest.  It's scary at times, but loads of fun! <p>Xaxia<BR>Erudite Wizardess<BR>22nd Season</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwalpus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>walpus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/29/00 8:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questing for lower mid levels...</span><hr size=1> Do others agree that a lvl 20 wiz could do this portion of the quest with little help?  Not that I doubt that you did it, I would just like some other's feedback :v)  BTW, what's a waterstone??? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uxaxia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xaxia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/29/00 11:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questing for lower mid levels...</span><hr size=1> A waterstone is a summoned item that casts Endure Breathing when you right click on it in an inventory slot.  It is necessary to have these to get the rods in Lake Rathe, Erud's Crossing, and Everfrost.  I used them at Oasis just to be safe, too.<br>
<br>
Any level 20 magician can summon these for you.  I did a &quot;/who all magician 20 60&quot; and offered some pp for a whole backpack full.  They are NO RENT by the way.<br>
<br>
I play on Lanys T'Vyl and found that any wizard that has done this will be more than happy to assist.  When I went into Guk, a level 49 wizard down there helped me greatly.  Thanks Xyntic!!!<br>
<br>
She showed me around and almost died herself.  I spent about 2 hours getting that rod.  Finally, a level 51 warrior escorted me to it, with another wizard who was doing the quest a second time.  The problem with Lower Guk is that there are undead and regular mobs there, so one form of invis does not work.  I never got aggroed on (it seemed that the froggies had an affinity for the high lvls) so I made it out unscathed.<br>
<br>
It is a scary quest to do, but I did it with a minimal amount of hand-holding.  If you're ever on Lanys T'Vyl, gimme a tell, and I'll answer any questions you have.<br>
<br>
Once complete, you'll carry your staff with pride! <p>Xaxia<BR>Erudite Wizardess<BR>22nd Season</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/upolanthis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Polanthis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/17/00 9:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questing for lower mid levels...</span><hr size=1> Well I would recommend doing the Acumen Mask quest and the Runescale Cloak quest at your lvl. All the items you will need for both quests will be very easy to get with maybe the exception of the Lizzy cloak in Cazic as it is a highly camped spot. Other than that you should have no trouble getting the items to get both the mask and the cloak and you will like the reward of both items.<br>
<br>
Polanthis Dethrainer<br>
44 Wizard<br>
The Rathe <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/upolanthis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Polanthis</A> at: 10/17/00 7:37:38 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujinnikinicleornian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jinnikinic  Leornian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/19/00 7:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questing for lower mid levels...</span><hr size=1> Hello,<br>
<br>
You didnt mention in your post what quests you have already done but two of the best quests for low to mid levels are in Qeynos. The Band of Rodcet Nife (+3 int +10 mana) and the Cutbert quest ( gold stud earring +3 int). I did both of these quests solo at level 16 but they are probably doable at a lower level than that.<br>
<br>
As for the staff of the wheel, I agree that this quest can be done in the 20's. I did this quest at level 25. You might as well go ahead and do it and expect to die a few times. If you wait till you are actually old enough to kill the mobs guarding the rods you will be waiting a long time.<br>
<br>
The quests in the Temple of Solusek Ro can all be done in your mid to high 20's but it helps to have a group for these.<br>
<br>
Have fun and good luck<br>
Jinnikinic Leornian<br>
lvl 42 wizard<br>
Company of Valor<br>
Quellious <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uminornegative.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MinorNegative</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/12/00 3:22 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questing for lower mid levels...</span><hr size=1> I did this quest at level 30, Mainly because I was lazy. I just bought some Enduring Breath potions from a vendor. Probably more expensive but, eh. <br>
